disruption%20to%20operations%2C%20and%20avoid%20being%20charged%20with%20hefty%20fees%20if%20they%20lack%20accurate%20employment-authorization%20documents%20known%20as%20I-9s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreparing%20for%20an%20ICE%20raid%20may%20be%20especially%20relevant%20for%20employers%20in%20industries%20such%20as%20food%20processing%20and%20construction%2C%20they%20say%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eas%20these%20typically%20rely%20on%20immigrant%20labor.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20workers%20are%20already%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fice-raids-business-sales-down-low-foot-traffic-immigrant-neighrbodhood-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20showing%20up%20for%20shifts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20fearful%20of%20getting%20swept%20up%20in%20raids%20%E2%80%94%20though%20the%20arrival%20of%20armed%20agents%20in%20the%20workplace%20could%20be%20scary%20for%20anyone.%20ICE%20did%20not%20comment%20for%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20responsibility%20to%20protect%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kim%20Minnick%2C%20an%20HR%20consultant%20in%20Napa%2C%20California%2C%20who%20developed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcodetravellerhr.notion.site%2FRapid-Response-Template-17fc390a0f86802b9007ea3a9eb748af%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erapid%20response%20template%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Immigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%20raids%20earlier%20this%20year%20and%20posted%20it%20online%20to%20share%20with%20her%20industry%20peers.%20It%20features%20tips%20such%20as%20keeping%20within%20arm's%20reach%20a%20list%20of%20emergency%20contacts%20for%20any%20workers%20who%20get%20detained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20may%20have%20minors%20waiting%20to%20be%20picked%20up%20at%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20Minnick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ICE%20raid%20at%20Glen%20Valley%20Foods%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686d8570f748d8c055f53326%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221467%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmployees%20and%20ICE%20agents%20stand%20outside%20Glenn%20Valley%20Foods%20meat%20production%20plant%20in%20Omaha%2C%20Nebraska.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Immigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%2Fvia%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202ef0169-51f5-4542-8f27-4eb7f787e6c0%5C%22%3EMore%20workplace%20raids%20expected%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20January%2C%20ICE%20has%20highlighted%20arrests%20made%20at%20worksites%20across%20the%20country%2C%20including%20a%20meat-processing%20plant%20in%20Omaha%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20a%20fire-equipment%20company%20in%20Kings%20Mountain%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20and%20a%20Louisiana%20racetrack.%20It's%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20meet%20the%20Trump%20administration's%203%2C000%20arrest-per-day%20minimum.%20The%20administration%20has%20attributed%20the%20effort%20to%20protecting%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWorksite%20enforcement%20remains%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20our%20efforts%20to%20safeguard%20public%20safety%2C%20national%20security%2C%20and%20economic%20stability%2C%26quot%3B%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20spokeswoman%20Tricia%20McLaughlin%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EICE%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehasn't%20specified%20how%20many%20workplaces%20have%20been%20raided%20overall%2C%20though%20more%20visits%20could%20be%20on%20the%20horizon.%20Last%20week%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20signed%20into%20law%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhs.gov%2Fnews%2F2025%2F07%2F04%2Fsecretary-noem-commends-president-trump-and-one-big-beautiful-bill-signing-law%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebill%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20provides%20ICE%20with%20additional%20funding%20and%20resources%20to%20go%20after%20undocumented%20immigrants%2C%20including%20enough%20detention%20capacity%20to%20maintain%20an%20average%20daily%20population%20of%20100%2C000%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb907080-e497-4cf1-998b-54901e76b6a8%5C%22%3EDeveloping%20a%20plan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20are%20already%20mandated%20by%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20have%20at%20least%20a%20generic%20emergency%20response%20plan%20that%20is%20up%20to%20date%2C%20though%20not%20all%20do%2C%20said%20Bo%20Mitchell%2C%20president%20of%20911%20Consulting%20in%20Wilton%2C%20Connecticut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suspects%20that%20some%20company%20leaders%20are%20fearful%20that%20preparing%20for%20the%20possibility%20of%20an%20ICE%20raid%20in%20particular%20could%20be%20misinterpreted%20externally%20to%20mean%20they're%20harboring%20undocumented%20workers%20or%20engaging%20in%20a%20political%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20wants%20to%20talk%20about%20it%20because%20of%20overtones%20of%20politics%2C%26quot%3B%20Mitchell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20those%20who%20don't%20take%20such%20caution%20may%20be%20putting%20their%20credibility%20at%20risk%2C%20said%20Michelle%20Sinning%2C%20a%20principal%20at%20Bernstein%20Crisis%20Management%20in%20Mission%20Viejo%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20competence%20may%20come%20into%20question%20if%20you're%20not%20able%20to%20handle%20a%20high-pressure%20situation%20with%20confidence%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20can%20also%20face%20fines%20in%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20for%20every%20employee%20lacking%20proper%20I-9%20documentation%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20surprise%20audit%20by%20ICE%20or%20another%20government%20entity%2C%20said%20Tina%20Ullmann%2C%20an%20HR%20consultant%20in%20Milford%2C%20Connecticut.%20Even%20a%20clerical%20error%20can%20be%20costly%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280f5357d-fbfd-4ebe-9d59-2a7f2f6b77c3%5C%22%3EPreparing%20for%20an%20ICE%20visit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20ensuring%20those%20I-9s%20are%20compliant%2C%20employers%20should%20train%20workers%20who%20greet%20visitors%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20escort%20any%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EICE%20agents%20who%20show%20up%20to%20an%20area%20that%20isn't%20private%20but%20won't%20interfere%20with%20customers%20or%20other%20employees%2C%20such%20as%20a%20conference%20room%2C%20said%20immigration%20attorney%20Christine%20Rodriguez%20in%20Atlanta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20workers%20should%20then%20know%20to%20alert%20the%20right%20personnel%20to%20interact%20with%20the%20agents%2C%20such%20as%20the%20company's%20CEO%2C%20head%20of%20HR%2C%20or%20lead%20counsel%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EICE%20agents%20are%20not%20legally%20permitted%20to%20access%20private%20areas%20of%20a%20workplace%20without%20a%20judicial%20warrant%2C%20which%20will%20say%20%26quot%3BU.S.%20District%20Court%26quot%3B%20and%20bear%20the%20signature%20of%20a%20federal%20judge%2C%20said%20Evan%20Fray-Witzer%2C%20an%20immigration%20lawyer%20in%20Boston.%20By%20contrast%2C%20he%20said%20administrative%20warrants%20do%20not%20legally%20grant%20such%20access%20and%20so%20employers%20would%20be%20within%20their%20rights%20to%20deny%20entry%20to%20ICE%20agents%20bearing%20only%20one%20of%20those.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeadership%20or%20employees%20should%20never%20interfere%20with%20ICE%20agents'%20actions%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they%20believe%20their%20actions%20to%20be%20illegal%20%E2%80%94%20or%20they%20could%20face%20obstruction%20charges%2C%20warned%20Fray-Witzer.%20Instead%2C%20he%20suggested%20trying%20to%20document%20the%20incident%20by%20recording%20video%20or%20taking%20notes%2C%20as%20these%20could%20come%20in%20handy%20should%20the%20matter%20lead%20to%20a%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20benefit%20to%20the%20employer%20or%20the%20employee%20to%20try%20and%20talk%20ICE%20out%20of%20taking%20someone%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fray-Witzer.%20%26quot%3BThe%20best%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20get%20as%20much%20information%20as%20you%20possibly%20can.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3