Ukraine%20needs%2C%20but%20what%20they%20need%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20tactics%20and%20weaponry%2C%20to%20be%20ready%20for%20a%20possible%20war%20with%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b48218b-a52b-454e-a607-7134d6f2cffb%5C%22%3EProtecting%20NATO%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Baltic%20countries%20are%20among%20the%20most%20vocal%20countries%20in%20Europe%20about%20the%20Russian%20threat%20given%20their%20proximity%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20alone.%20A%20host%20of%20nations%2C%20including%20the%20UK%2C%20Germany%2C%20France%2C%20Finland%2C%20and%20Denmark%2C%20have%20all%20warned%20that%20Russia%20could%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20CIA%20director%20David%20Petraeus%20warned%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20Lithuania%20is%20the%20most%20likely%20NATO%20country%20to%20be%20invaded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO's%20collective%20defense%20clause%20means%20that%20an%20attack%20on%20any%20one%20country%20is%20an%20attack%20on%20the%20alliance.%20A%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20an%20alliance%20member%20could%20quickly%20spiral%20into%20a%20major%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllies%20have%20invested%20resources%20like%20troops%20and%20weaponry%20in%20those%20front-line%20countries%2C%20with%20the%20head%20of%20NATO%20calling%20them%20and%20neighboring%20Poland%20%26quot%3Ba%20first%20line%20of%20defense%26quot%3B%20in%20May.%20A%20Russian%20advance%20would%20ideally%20be%20stopped%20there%2C%20but%20those%20countries%20may%20only%20be%20able%20to%20slow%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20wearing%20camouflage%20gear%20and%20holding%20a%20firearm%20stands%20with%20his%20leg%20on%20a%20step%20on%20a%20camouflage-covered%20armored%20vehicle%20with%20more%20similar%20vehicles%20behind%20him%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686d21de3d5881a51c1cdbd4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENATO%20countries%20are%20training%20and%20exercising%20in%20the%20Baltic%20states%2C%20like%20in%20the%20Iron%20Wolf%20military%20exercises%20with%20NATO%20forces%20and%20partners%20in%20Lithuania%20in%20May%202025.%3Cp%3EPaulius%20Peleckis%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPevkur%20said%20it's%20important%20for%20all%20of%20NATO%20to%20help%20the%20region%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20eastern%20flank%20is%20the%20front%20door%20of%20NATO%2C%20so%20we%20need%20to%20keep%20it%20closed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllies%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20also%20have%20troops%20in%20the%20Baltic%20states%2C%20and%20allied%20F-35s%20are%20often%20deployed%20there%20as%20part%20of%20NATO's%20Baltic%20Air%20Policing%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Baltic%20countries%20have%20also%20taken%20strong%20action%20themselves%2C%20not%20merely%20relying%20on%20more%20powerful%20countries%20for%20protection.%20They%20spend%20among%20the%20highest%20in%20NATO%20on%20defense%20as%20a%20proportion%20of%20their%20GDP%20and%20lead%20calls%20for%20the%20alliance%20to%20massively%20increase%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20resources%20have%20not%20just%20been%20going%20into%20HIMARS.%20They%20are%20also%20buying%20missiles%2C%20howitzers%2C%20air%20defense%20systems%2C%20ammunition%2C%20and%20other%20weaponry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20their%20choices%20have%20been%20informed%20by%20the%20way%20Russia%20is%20fighting%20and%20what%20is%20working%20for%20Ukraine.%20Vaidotas%20Urbelis%2C%20the%20policy%20director%20of%20Lithuania's%20defense%20ministry%2C%20told%20BI%20last%20year%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-neighbor-lithuania-buying-first-tanks-due-ukraine-lessons-official-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehis%20military%20was%20buying%20tanks%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20its%20history%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20this%20war%20had%20shown%20them%20to%20be%20important.%20Tanks%20have%20faced%20serious%20challenges%20in%20this%20war%2C%20but%20they%20still%20have%20a%20role.%3C%2Fp