C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ruling-trump-firings-federal-agencies-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETuesday's%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20their%20jobs%20landed%20with%20a%20thud%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20shock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOmfg%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Department%20of%20Justice%20employee%20responded%20when%20a%20reporter%20broke%20the%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20months%2C%20thousands%20of%20federal%20government%20employees%20have%20watched%20the%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20tennis%20match%3A%20a%20legal%20back-and-forth%20between%20the%20White%20House%20and%20various%20unions%20and%20advocacy%20groups%20over%20DOGE's%20plan%20to%20remake%20the%20federal%20workforce%2C%20with%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20jobs%20at%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%20afternoon%2C%20workers%20got%20an%20answer%20many%20had%20been%20dreading.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supremecourt.gov%2Fopinions%2F24pdf%2F24a1174_h3ci.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20proceed%20with%20widespread%20staff%20cuts%20at%20federal%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20agencies%20will%20follow%20through%20with%20their%20reduction-in-force%20plans%20%E2%80%94%20and%20on%20what%20timeline%20%E2%80%94%20is%20still%20uncertain.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-stick-around-despite-stepping-back-doge-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%20has%20said%20he%20has%20stepped%20back%20from%20DOGE%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it's%20unclear%20how%20much%20sway%20the%20cost-cutting%20outfit%20still%20has%20in%20directing%20widespread%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20news%20broke%2C%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%2016%20current%20federal%20employees%20across%20agencies%20to%20gauge%20their%20responses.%20Some%20were%20frustrated%20by%20the%20highest%20courts'%20decision%2C%20while%20others%20said%20they%20worry%20essential%20government%20services%20could%20be%20at%20risk.%20Most%20used%20words%20like%20%26quot%3Bfear%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Buncertainty%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bdisheartening%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbleak%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20the%20current%20energy%20within%20their%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20employees%20asked%20to%20remain%20anonymous%20for%20fear%20of%20professional%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20us%20were%20feeling%20like%20we%20could%20breathe%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service%20worker%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20feeling%20turned%20on%20a%20dime%20today.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294d3d83f-d831-4bb2-b1d0-24a2e1966e27%5C%22%3E'We%20just%20pretend%20it's%20not%20happening'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20federal%20workers%20told%20BI%20that%20they've%20been%20anxiously%20checking%20their%20inboxes%20and%20coworker%20group%20chats%20since%20cuts%20began%20last%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20said%20they%20were%20stunned%20by%20the%20SCOTUS%20ruling%20and%20worried%20about%20their%20future%20livelihoods.%20A%20few%20said%20they%20have%20had%20to%20take%20on%20a%20heavier%20workload%20amid%20staffing%20changes%2C%20and%20have%20seen%20morale%20tank%20among%20their%20coworkers.%20Others%20described%20the%20stress%20of%20financial%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20appears%20to%20me%20as%20though%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20acquiesced%20to%20the%20executive%20branch%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Edwin%20Osario%2C%20a%20worker%20at%20the%20Social%20Security%20Administration.%20The%20result%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20that%20hard-working%20and%20dedicated%20civil%20servants%20will%20lose%20their%20jobs%2C%20and%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20lose%20their%20careers%20that%20were%20predicated%20on%20serving%20the%20American%20public.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20see%20any%20of%20this%20ending%20well%2C%20and%20I'm%20scared%20for%20my%20country%2C%20my%20children's%20future%2C%20and%20my%20job%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Department%20of%20Defense%20Employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20however%2C%20weren't%20surprised.%20As%20one%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20employee%20put%20it%2C%20the%20feeling%20they%20%26quot%3Bcould%20be%20pushed%20out%20at%20any%20moment%26quot%3B%20is%20something%20they've%20carried%20to%20work%20every%20day%20for%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20planning%20to%20hear%20we're%20RIF'ed%20any%20week%20since%20it%20went%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20an%20employee%20at%20the%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration.%20They%20anticipate%20they'll%20lose%20their%20job%20and%20will%20probably%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Bpublish%20data%20and%20reports%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%20to%20tie%20up%20loose%20ends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service%20employee%20said%20they%20avoid%20thinking%20about%20staff%20cuts%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20only%20way%20I'm%20keeping%20sane%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%20%26quot%3BNobody%20at%20work%20talks%20about%20it.%20There's%20nothing%20we%20can%20do%2C%20so%20we%20just%20pretend%20it's%20not%20happening.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20one%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20employee%20saw%20the%20SCOTUS%20news%20alert%20on%20their%20phone%20Tuesday%20afternoon%2C%20they%20said%20they%20just%20%26quot%3Bpacked%20up%20and%20left%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20knew%20they%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20focus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20via%20Signal%20at%20alicetecotzky.05%2C%20julianakaplan.33%2C%20asheffey.97%2C%20and%20alliekelly.10.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3Ehere%E2%80%99s%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223130d46a-eea0-4a31-8e22-dcd8529109ae%5C%22%3EGovernment%20employees%20are%20worried%20about%20the%20future%20of%20public%20services%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20stemmed%20from%20challenges%20to%20a%20February%20executive%20order%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bcritical%20transformation%20of%20the%20Federal%20bureaucracy.%26quot%3B%20The%20order%20tasked%20DOGE%20with%20carrying%20out%20%26quot%3Blarge-scale%20reductions%20in%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20spokesperson%20Harrison%20Fields%20called%20the%20ruling%20%26quot%3Banother%20definitive%20victory%20for%20the%20President%20and%20his%20administration%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20pushed%20back%20against%20what%20he%20described%20as%20partisan%20attempts%20to%20obstruct%20government%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocal%20governments%2C%20advocacy%20groups%2C%20and%20unions%20like%20the%20American%20Federation%20of%20Government%20Employees%20sued%20over%20the%20order%20in%20April%2C%20and%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20California%20blocked%20the%20order%20in%20May.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20granted%20a%20stay%20on%20that%20injunction%2C%20which%20means%20thousands%20of%20current%20and%20reinstated%20workers%20could%20now%20lose%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuestions%20still%20remain.%20It's%20not%20yet%20known%20how%20the%20decision%20could%20play%20out%20at%20individual%20agencies%20or%20exactly%20how%20many%20jobs%20are%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20unsigned%20opinion%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20it%20is%20taking%20%26quot%3Bno%20view%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20substance%20of%20the%20Trump%