pecially%20if%20they%E2%80%99re%20perceived%20as%20moralizing.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20undermines%20the%20user%20experience%20and%20can%20backfire%2C%20especially%20for%20people%20who%20come%20to%20chatbots%20seeking%20a%20nonjudgmental%20space%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FPiqIs%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22preachy%20ai%20trigger%20warnings%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22415%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d67f0fea-7b99-4622-a1ac-616923010eee%5C%22%3EEven%20when%20you%20want%20to%20do%20bad%20things%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20companies%20aren%E2%80%99t%20just%20worried%20about%20preachiness%20on%20everyday%20topics.%20They%E2%80%99re%20also%20training%20their%20AI%20bots%20to%20avoid%20a%20holier-than-thou%20tone%20in%20situations%20involving%20harmful%20or%20hateful%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaFreniere%20said%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20truly%20neutral%20bot%20is%20wishful%20thinking.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20actually%20a%20fantasy%2C%20this%20idea%20of%20not%20being%20judgmental%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBy%20nature%2C%20we%20as%20humans%20make%20judgments%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20in%20all%20the%20training%20data.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20even%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Cneutral%E2%80%9D%20bots%20are%20always%20making%20value%20calls.%20%E2%80%9CIts%20algorithm%20is%2C%20to%20an%20extent%2C%20a%20judgment-making%20algorithm%2C%E2%80%9D%20LaFreniere%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20all%20moral%20territory%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20the%20bot%20tries%20not%20to%20sound%20heavy-handed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20from%20Google%E2%80%99s%20project%20Mint%20shows%20that%20an%20answer%2C%20which%20the%20doc%20labels%20%E2%80%9Cneutral%2C%E2%80%9D%20makes%20a%20judgme