ble%20work%20than%20it%20can%20do%20today%2C%20and%20in%20the%20fullness%20of%20time%2C%20can%20do%20every%20piece%20of%20valuable%20work%20that%20humans%20can%20do.%20We%20want%20to%20enable%20this%20full%20automation%20and%20thereby%20generate%20enormous%20amounts%20of%20value%20for%20society.%20That%20is%20the%20thing%20that%20we're%20focused%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20want%20to%20do%20that%20by%20building%20the%20piece%20that%20I%20think%20is%20most%20neglected%20in%20AI%20development%20today%2C%20which%20is%20scaling%20up%20the%20RL%20%E2%80%94reinforcement%20learning%20%E2%80%94%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat's%20so%20you%20get%20scalable%20labor.%20Is%20that%20the%20idea%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20right.%20AI%20is%20scalable%20in%20a%20way%20that%20humans%20are%20not.%20You%20can%20copy%20and%20spin%20up%20a%20very%20large%20number%20of%20them%2C%20and%20you're%20not%20bottlenecked%20by%20something%20like%20human%20population%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20economy%20today%20is%20very%20much%20bottlenecked%20by%20labor.%20Capital%20is%20something%20that%20you%20could%20invest%2C%20and%20you%20can%20generate%20more%20however%20fast%20you%20want%2C%20basically.%20But%20with%20humans%2C%20population%20growth%20is%20like%202%25%20or%203%25%20per%20year%2C%20and%20that%20is%20not%20something%20that%20you%20could%20invest%20in%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0increasing%20the%20size%20of%20your%20population%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0very%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20presents%20the%20opportunity%20to%20do%20precisely%20that.%20You%20can%20reinvest%20your%20output%20into%20building%20more%20data%20centers%20and%20compute%2C%20and%20you%20can%20just%20run%20more%20AI%20workers.%20That%20grows%20your%20economy%2C%20which%20you%20can%20then%20reinvest%20again.%20That%20creates%20this%20feedback%20loop%20that%20results%20in%20this%20acceleration%20in%20overall%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20you%20start%20with%20trying%20to%20automate%20software%20engineering%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoftware%20engineering%20makes%20sense%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20reasons.%20So%20one%20is%2C%20there%20is%20an%20existing%20technology%20and%20culture%20for%20writing%20very%20good%20tests%20%E2%80%94%20tests%20that%20check%20whether%20the%20piece%20of%20software%20is%20working%20as%20intended.%20Whether%20it's%20not%20breaking%3B%20whether%20it's%20not%20buggy%3B%20whether%20it's%20not%20surfacing%20security%20problems.%20And%20that%20is%20really%20helpful%20for%20doing%20RL.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20in%20RL%2C%20you%20want%20some%20reward%20signal.%20You%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20tell%20the%20model%20you%20did%20the%20task%20correctly%20versus%20incorrectly.%20Then%20you%20want%20to%20leverage%20that%20to%20reinforce%20the%20kind%20of%20patterns%20of%20behavior%20that%20resulted%20in%20it%20correctly%20performing%20the%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20there%20is%20this%20battle%20to%20win%20coding%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-google-anthropic-ai-updates-gpt-gemini-claude-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20and%20Anthropic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20are%20really%20keen%20on%20winning%20that%20battle.%20They%20are%20very%20willing%20to%20spend%20a%20ton%20of%20money%20on%20beating%20their%20competitors.%20So%2C%20that%20is%20really%20great%20for%20us%2C%20because%20it%20makes%20it%20much%20easier%20for%20us%20to%20get%20lucrative%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere's%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20discussion%20about%20AI%20automating%20jobs.%20If%20this%20does%20occur%2C%20how%20will%20humanity%20get%20through%20this%20transition%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20be%20a%20gradual%20process.%20Some%20people%20in%20the%20industry%20expect%20this%20will%20happen%20very%2C%20very%20soon%20%E2%80%94%20this%20decade.%20I%20don't%20think%20that'll%20happen%20that%20soon.%20It'll%20be%20more%20of%20a%20challenge%20that%20takes%20decades%20for%20us%20to%20develop%20the%20technology%2C%20produce%20all%20the%20innovations%2C%20and%20build%20out%20our%20capital%20stock%2C%20and%20our%20compute%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that.%20But%20I%20agree%2C%20there%20will%20be%20this%20transition%2C%20and%20I%20think%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20more%20gradual%20and%20something%20that's%20drawn%20out%20over%20decades%20is%20definitely%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20believed%20it%20was%20something%20that%20would%20take%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20then%20I'd%20be%20much%20more%20nervous.%20Also%2C%20there%20are%20cases%20today%20where%20a%20large%20share%20of%20people's%20income%20in%20specific%20countries%20is%20not%20derived%20from%20labor%20income.%20There%20are%20some%20oil%20states%20that%20do%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20Norway%2C%20as%20an%20example%2C%20where%20the%20sovereign%20wealth%20fund%20is%20worth%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20I%20think%20we%20will%20look%20at%20examples%20like%20that%20for%20what%20our%20future%20might%20look%20like.%20Frankly%2C%20Norway%20is%20not%20that%20bad.%20I'm%20Dutch%20myself%2C%20and%20I%20have%20a%20bunch%20of%20Norwegian%20friends.%20They%20seem%20to%20do%20just%20fine.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20have%20higher%20standards%20of%20living%20than%20people%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20something%20that%20is%20indeed%20a%20large%20challenge%2C%20but%20I%20think%20the%20upside%20is%20just%20so%20enormous%20that%20the%20costs%20associated%20with%20this%20transition%20look%20fairly%20minor%20in%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20effect%20of%20that%20consumption%20could%20be%20increased%20externalities.%20If%20consumption%20is%20going%20up%2C%20for%20example%2C%20there%20are%20environmental%20costs.%20Have%20you%20thought%20about%20those%20types%20of%20things%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20externalities%20are%20concerning.%20The%20environmental%20impacts%20are%20real%2C%20but%20I%20think%20there%20are%20problems%20where%20technology%20enables%20us%20to%20really%20make%20a%20large%20dent%2C%20and%20the%20development%20of%20AI%20is%20this%20enormous%20accelerant%20for%20technological%20progress.%20The%20development%20of%20AI%2C%20I%20am%20fairly%20confident%2C%20will%20improve%20our%20ability%20to%20minimize%20the%20harms%20to%20the%20environment%20if%20we%20want%20to%20deploy%20AI%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20more%20worried%20about%20an%20acceleration%20of%20economic%20growth%20and%20technological%20change%2C%20like%20collapsing%20history.%20If%20you%20have%20this%20acceleration%2C%20then%20maybe%20100%20years%20of%20history%20could%20happen%20in%20one%20decade%2C%20because%20things%20just%20move%20a%20lot%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20might%20mean%20that%20the%20rates%20of%20things%20happening%20that%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20happen%2C%20like%20wars%20or%20various%20financial%20crises%20or%20pandemics%2C%20perhaps%20might%20accelerate%20because%20we're%20compressing%20time%2C%20effectively.%20So%2C%20that%20is%20maybe%20a%20worry%2C%20which%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20abstract%2C%20but%20I%20think%20that%20is%20the%20level%20of%20abstraction%20that%20is%20appropriate%20because%20it's%20hard%20to%20predict%20the%20details%20of%20precisely%20what%20will%20happen%20in%2010%2C%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20said%20you%20want%20to%20give%20everybody%20one%20answer%20about%20the%20implications%20for%20their%20jobs.%20But%20desk%20jobs%20you%20can%20do%20remotely%20feel%20more%20at%20risk%20than%20those%20of%20a%20nurse%20or%20a%20mechanic.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20for%20that%20reason%2C%20we%20don't%20have%20a%20robotics%20division%20just%20yet.%20Robotics%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20going%20to%20take%20a%20little%20longer%2C%20but%20eventually%20we%20want%20to%20get%20there%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20robotics%20is%20just%20behind%20the%20types%20of%20tasks%20that%20you%20can%20do%20remotely.%20So%2C%20for%20that%20reason%2C%20I%20think%20it%20makes%20sense%20for%20us%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20things%20that%20you%20can%20do%20remotely.%20There's%20just%20a%20larger%20market%20for%20that%20currently.%20But%20I'm%20also%20pretty%20encouraged%20by%20some%20of%20the%20progress%20in%20humanoid%20robotics%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that's%20really%20valuable.%20I%20would%20love%20to%20have%20a%20humanoid%20robot%20that%20is%20able%20to%20clean%20up%20my%20office%20and%20my%20home%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that'll%20be%20really%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20have%20the%20sense%20that%20you'll%20eventually%20be%20developing%20yourself%20out%20of%20a%20job%3F%20What%20would%20you%20do%20in%20that%20case%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20little%20ironic%20that%20we%20are%20hiring%20engineers%20to%20obsolete%20themselves%2C%20effectively%2C%20by%20building%20these%20environments%20that%20train%20models%20to%20be%20good%20at%20the%20types%20of%20things%20that%20they're%20good%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20they%20are%20working%20on%20hard%2C%20important%20problems%2C%20and%20they're%20getting%20rewarded%20well%20for%20it.%20If%20they%20join%20us%2C%20then%20they%20get%20equity.%20And%2C%20so%20even%20once%20they've%20obsoleted%20themselves%2C%20they'd%20still%20be%20able%20to%20become%20rich%20off%20that%2C%20by%20just%20owning%20equity.%20That's%20the%20pitch%20I%20give%20our%20software%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmechanize-use-ai-automate-every-job-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752136261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686eafce3d5881a51c1cfec1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmechanize-use-ai-automate-every-job-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tamay%20Besiroglu%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20startup%20Mechanize%2C%20want