20Green%20and%20Spiegel.%20She%20practiced%20during%20Trump's%20first%20term%2C%20when%20they%20learned%20%26quot%3Banything%20horrible%20can%20happen%20and%20nothing's%20really%20surprising%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20unfolded%20in%20a%20way%20where%20you%20can't%20count%20on%20what's%20constitutional.%20You%20can't%20count%20on%20what's%20legal.%20You%20can't%20count%20on%20what%20should%20happen.%20You%20can't%20count%20on%20what%20CBP%20tells%20you%20is%20going%20to%20happen.%20So%2C%20it's%20tough%20to%20nail%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20administration%20says%20it's%20heightening%20immigration%20scrutiny%20in%20order%20to%20quell%20illegal%20immigration%2C%20tighten%20the%20border%2C%20and%20protect%20Americans.%20But%20for%20some%20people%2C%20the%20only%20impact%20is%20that%20it's%20complicating%20their%20plans%20and%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decade-old%20reckless%20driving%20conviction%20is%20keeping%20Tori%2C%20from%20California%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20from%20holding%20their%20wedding%20celebration%20in%20Mexico%20this%20fall.%20She's%20American%3B%20he's%20a%20green-card%20holder%20from%20Mexico.%20He%20hasn't%20had%20a%20problem%20over%20the%20charge%20beyond%20a%20quick%20extra%20check%20at%20immigration%2C%20but%20now%2C%20they're%20afraid%20reentry%20may%20be%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETori%2C%20who%20asked%20that%20Business%20Insider%20withhold%20her%20last%20name%2C%20has%20been%20reading%20news%20articles%2C%20combing%20through%20message%20boards%2C%20and%20reaching%20out%20to%20people%20in%20similar%20situations%20online.%20In%20her%20search%20for%20answers%2C%20there's%20a%20flood%20of%20confusing%2C%20vague%20information%20floating%20around.%20%26quot%3BWe%20heard%20about%20people%20with%20green%20cards%20and%20misdemeanors%20just%20being%20detained%20for%20two%20months%20or%20even%20having%20court%20dates%20for%20deportation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BHe%20has%20been%20talking%20to%20his%20lawyers%2C%20but%20even%20they've%20been%20going%20back%20and%20forth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20worries%2C%20they've%20decided%20to%20postpone%20the%20event%20%E2%80%94%20a%20potentially%20pricey%20conclusion.%20She%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20were%20recently%20legally%20married%2C%20have%20already%20paid%20half%20of%20the%20cost%20for%20their%20wedding%2C%20and%20guests%20have%20already%20booked%20rooms%20and%20hotels.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20worth%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20If%20her%20husband%20were%20to%20be%20detained%2C%20their%20lawyers%20would%20probably%20be%20able%20to%20get%20him%20out%2C%20but%20the%20couple%20worry%20that%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20he%20could%20lose%20his%20job%20and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20they%20could%20lose%20their%20house.%20Luckily%2C%20the%20resort%20where%20they're%20holding%20the%20wedding%20has%20been%20understanding%20about%20holding%20off.%20They're%20now%20waiting%20on%20her%20husband's%20citizenship%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%2C%20from%20Illinois%2C%20has%20been%20a%20%26quot%3BRoman%20history%20nerd%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20so%20she%20and%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%20were%20excited%20to%20go%20to%20Italy%20for%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-went-on-honeymoon-alone-by-myself-solo-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehoneymoon%3C%2Fa%3E%20later%20this%20year%20and%20maybe%20swing%20by%20some%20parts%20of%20England%2C%20where%20she%20studied%20abroad.%20Her%20fianc%C3%A9%20is%20from%20South%20Korea%20and%20has%20been%20living%20in%20the%20US%20as%20a%20permanent%20resident%20for%2020%20years%2C%20but%20they%20feel%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-summer-travel-americans-economic-uncertainty-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrip%20to%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20too%20risky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20if%20we%20went%20through%20entry%20100%20times%2C%20would%20it%20go%20well%2095%25%20of%20the%20time%3F%20Probably%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20But%20all%20you%20need%20is%20one%20customs%20agent%20%26quot%3Bwho%20has%20decided%20that%20it's%20his%20mission%20in%20life%20to%20bring%20about%20Trump's%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna's%20frustration%20with%20the%20situation%20is%20palpable.%20Her%20partner%20is%20a%20lawyer%2C%20and%20she's%20getting%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20finance.%20They%20have%20a%20solid%20middle-class%20income%20and%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20quote-unquote%20doing%20it%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20none%20of%20that%20really%20matters%20for%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20considering%20honeymoon%20options%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOh%20no%2C%20I%20can't%20take%20my%20vacation%2C%26quot%3B%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20privileged%20problem%2C%20but%20problems%20are%20problems%2C%20and%20for%20many%20travelers%2C%20this%20is%20a%20new%20one.%20Some%20people%20are%20scared%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20they%20call%20home%2C%20even%20if%20they%20plan%20to%20set%20down%20temporary%20stakes%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20not%20be%20let%20back%20in.%20Their%20loved%20ones%20are%20on%20edge%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreen-card%20holders%20are%20generally%20allowed%20to%20leave%20and%20reenter%20the%20US%2C%20and%20they%20have%20a%20legal%20right%20to%20return%20unless%20a%20judge%20revokes%20it.%20As%20with%20US%20citizens%2C%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20can%20ask%20green-card%20holders%20questions%2C%20but%20they%20can't%20require%20them%20to%20unlock%20their%20devices%20or%20hand%20over%20their%20passwords%20in%20searches.%20CBP%20has%20much%20more%20discretion%20to%20deny%20entry%20to%20people%20who%20are%20living%20in%20the%20country%20on%20a%20visa%2C%20such%20as%20for%20studying%2C%20tourism%2C%20or%20work.%20It%20could%20be%20because%20of%20a%20criminal%20record%2C%20because%20of%20some%20social%20media%20posts%2C%20or%20because%20the%20agent%20feels%20something%20about%20someone's%20story%20doesn't%20add%20up%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20immigration%20intent.%20In%20these%20cases%2C%20they%20can%20search%20devices%2C%20detain%20people%2C%20and%20tell%20them%20to%20turn%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20laws%20surrounding%20immigration%20haven't%20radically%20changed%2C%20scrutiny%20from%20border%20agents%20has%20increased.%20In%20the%20US%20and%20abroad%2C%20there%20are%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20news%20stories%20about%20people%20being%20detained%20or%20denied%20reentry%20for%20what%20to%20many%20people%20may%20seem%20like%20inane%20and%20unclear%20reasons.%20And%20regardless%20of%20a%20person's%20status%2C%20Karahan%20says%2C%20border%20agents%20are%20testing%20the%20limits%20for%20everyone%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20they%20ask%20and%20try%20to%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20dicey%20area%2C%20because%20the%20agencies%20are%20all%20pushing%20what's%20actually%20legal%20and%20what's%20constitutional%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGadi%20Zohar%2C%20an%20immigration%20lawyer%20in%20New%20York%2C%20says%20he%20usually%20tells%20clients%20that%20if%20they're%20in%20the%20US%20on%20a%20green%20card%2C%20there%20probably%20won't%20be%20an%20issue%2C%20but%20it's%20%26quot%3Btricky%26quot%3B%20with%20visas.%20If%20a%20person%20were%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20and%20the%20US%20government%20enacted%20a%20travel%20ban%20on%20their%20home%20country%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20Zohar%20says%2C%20they%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20return.%20%26quot%3BSo%20if%20you're%20on%20a%20visa%2C%20I%20usually%20suggest%20staying%20in%20the%20US%20if%20you%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Particularly%20if%20it's%20a%20discretionary%20trip%2C%20like%20a%20bachelorette%20party%20or%20honeymoon%2C%20he%20advises%20erring%20on%20the%20side%20of%20caution.%20A%20year%20ago%2C%20this%20wasn't%20really%20something%20he%20was%20telling%20many%20of%20his%20clients%20to%20worry%20about%2C%20because%20CBP%20wasn't%20as%20aggressive%20as%20it%20is%20now.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20sort%20of%20searching%20to%20find%20things%20versus%20if%20something%20came%20up%2C%20they%20would%20handle%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarahan%2C%20similarly%2C%20isn't%20cautioning%20green-card%20holders%20as%20much%2C%20though%20if%20they're%20from%20a%20country%20with%20a%20travel%20ban%2C%20such%20as%20Venezuela%20or%20Sierra%20Leone%2C%20she%20would%20worry.%20Her%20firm%20is%20warning%20everyone%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bmindful%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20social%20media.%20(Different%20lawyers%20have%20different%20stances%20on%20some%20of%20this%20%E2%80%94%20Stephen%20Yale-Loehr%2C%20a%20retired%20Cornell%20law%20professor%2C%20tells%20me%20everyone%20who%20is%20a%20noncitizen%20should%20worry%20about%20international%20travel%2C%20including%20green-card%20holders.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20client%20is%20different%20%E2%80%94%20for%20many%20clients%20with%20no%20known%20risk%20factors%2C%20we%20are%20advising%20they%20can%20travel%20as%20usual%20with%20certain%20caveats.%20For%20other%20clients%2C%20we%20are%20advising%20against%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Karahan%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20emailed%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20a%20CBP%20spokesperson%20says%20that%20a%20sharp%20decline%20in%20illegal%20immigration%20under%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20allowed%20law%20enforcement%20personnel%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20back%20to%20doing%20law%20enforcement%20work%2C%20like%20conducting%20thorough%20vetting%20and%20interviews.%26quot%3B%20They%20say%20lawful%20travelers%20should%20have%20nothing%20to%20fear%20from%20these%20measures%2C%20but%20if%20statuses%20or%20visa%20terms%20are%20violated%2C%20travelers%20may%20be%20subject%20to%20detention%20and%20removal.%20%26quot%3BA%20visa%20is%20a%20privilege%2C%20not%20a%20right%2C%20and%20only%20those%20who%20respect%20our%20laws%20and%20follow%20the%20proper%20procedures%20will%20be%20welcomed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20on%20green%20cards%20feel%20that%20leaving%20is%20too%20big%20of%20a%20risk.%20Jos%C3%A9%2C%20now%20in%20his%20mid-40s%2C%20was%20born%20in%20Mexico%20but%20has%20been%20in%20the%20US%20since%20he%20was%209%20years%20old.%20He%20has%20a%20felony%20conviction%20from%20nearly%2030%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20he's%20been%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20country%20plenty%20since%20without%20issue.%20Now%2C%20however%2C%20his%20attorney%20has%20advised%20him%20not%20to%20leave.%20He's%20the%20only%20member%20of%20his%20family%20who%20isn't%20a%20citizen%2C%20so%20his%20predicament%20is%20causing%20chaos%20for%20everyone's%20plans.%20They've%20canceled%20a%20trip%20to%20Canc%C3%BAn%2C%20Mexico%2C%20for%20his%20mother's%2072nd%20birthday%20and%20a%20trip%20to%20Jamaica%20with%20his%20youngest%20child.%20His%20lawyer%20says%20it's%20not%20worth%20leaving%20if%20it's%20not%20an%20emergency%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20even%20if%20it's%20an%20emergency%2C%20reconsider%20your%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20people%20already%20in%20the%20US%20who%20are%20adjusting%20their%20plans.%20Charlotte%20Eaton%2C%20a%20film%20producer%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20was%20invited%20to%20travel%20to%20a%20film%20festival%20in%20Miami%20earlier%20this%20year.%20It%20was%20an%20exciting%20opportunity%2C%20but%20then%20she%20started%20thinking%20about%20the%20news%20stories%20about%20tourists%20traveling%20to%20America%20who%20had%20been%20detained%20%E2%80%94%20specifically%2C%20one%20about%20a%2028-year-old%20woman%20from%20Wales%20who%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcly67j35y99o%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheld%20for%20two%20weeks%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20traveling%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Canada.%20Ultimately%2C%20Eaton%20decided%20to%20forgo%20the%20trip.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20very%20excited%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20in%20the%20same%20moment%2C%20I%20had%20this%20immediate%20gut%20instinct%20and%20said%2C%20'I'm%20not%20going%20to%20go%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20all%20seems%20a%20little%20bit%20hectic%20and%20crazy%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20to%20risk%20that%20for%20a%20three-day%20film%20festival.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaia%20Mindel%2C%20an%20economist%20from%20Argentina%2C%20has%20a%20similar%20reaction%2C%20especially%20after%20seeing%20a%20story%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fnews%2Fthe-lede%2Fhow-my-reporting-on-the-columbia-protests-led-to-my-deportation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20Yorker%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20an%20Australian%20man%20who%20was%20deported%20and%20compelled%20to%20share%20some%2C%20let's%20say%2C%20extra-private%20photos%20in%20the%20process.%20She%20usually%20travels%20to%20the%20US%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20year.%20Now%2C%20she's%20weighing%20whether%20to%20go%20to%20a%20conference%20she's%20been%20invited%20to%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20have%20to%20think%20about%20this%20decision%20and%20say%2C%20'What's%20the%20real%20risk%2C%20and%20what's%20the%20real%20problem%20that%20could%20come%20if%20I%20traveled%20to%20the%20US%20and%20get%20in%20trouble%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20As%20of%20now%2C%20she's%20inclined%20to%20stay%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20great%20for%20the%20US%20economy%20or%20business%20owners%20that%20foreigners%20are%20afraid%20to%20come%20to%20the%20US.%20It's%20a%20hit%20to%20sectors%20that%20depend%20on%20foreign%20visitors%2C%20and%20for%20companies%20that%20need%20to%20bring%20foreigners%20over%2C%20even%20if%20for%20a%20visit%2C%20it%20mucks%20up%20plans.%20Karahan%20says%20her%20firm%20has%20seen%20sports%20tournaments%20facing%20issues%20getting%20the%20staff%20needed%20for%20events%20because%20of%20changes%20in%20attitudes%20toward%20visitor%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlbert%20Paz%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20Gabriel's%20Travel%20Agency%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%20has%20been%20helping%20his%20clients%20change%20and%20cancel%20travel%20plans%20in%20reaction%20to%20the%20political%20environment.%20%26quot%3BWe%20deal%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20from%20Hispanic%20backgrounds%2C%20Arabic%20backgrounds%2C%20so%20it's%20a%20big%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20In%20light%20of%20immigration%20concerns%2C%20people%20are%20thinking%20twice%20about%20where%20they%20go%20and%20when%20they%20want%20to%20travel%2C%20and%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-strikes-iran-nuclear-program-response-war-risk-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econflict%20with%20Iran%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20has%20prompted%20even%20more%20reconsiderations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20been%20changing%20from%20their%20European%20destinations%2C%20South%20American%20destinations%2C%20to%20more%20local%20and%20Caribbean%20destinations%20just%20to%20feel%20more%20comfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20For%20families%20in%20particular%2C%20the%20decision-making%20can%20be%20especially%20challenging.%20%26quot%3BSummertime%20travel%20is%20mostly%20families%20that%20are%20going%20away%2C%20and%20the%20first%20thing%20on%20their%20mind%20are%20their%20children.%20The%20last%20thing%20anybody%20wants%20to%20do%20is%20get%20stuck%20in%20another%20country%2C%20have%20problems%20at%20the%20airport.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EVacation%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20fun%20and%20relaxing.%20The%20point%20of%20traveling%20with%20others%20is%20to%20connect%20while%20disconnecting%20from%20the%20day-to-day.%20People%20go%20abroad%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-for-international-travel-with-kids%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshow%20the%20world%20to%20their%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20celebrate%20with%20their%20partners%2C%20to%20ex